name: Laura Tatom
text: I’m really not sure what’s taken me so long to leave a review for Lake Martin Creamery! It’s hands down my favorite ice cream/custard place, and my favorite spot on Lake Martin. Stopping here is a MUST. Every single time I’ve been (and that number is too high to count) the treats have been on point. The owners genuinely care about their customers and their restaurant. Anything you pick will be delicious, from sundaes to shakes to sno-cones. I cannot recommend Lake Martin Creamery enough.

resp.text: Thanks Laura. We appreciate you. We have the best customers in the best community. We are truly blessed.

text: This was our second time here. The 1st time I had the blueberry cheesecake sundae and my husband had a banana shake. We both loved them. Absolutely so smooth and delicious. This time we all had a sundae, 1 caramel, one strawberry cheesecake sundae and a kids cup of chocolate with gummie bears. Again all were absolutely delicious!! We love this place and highly recommend it.

resp.text: We are so pleased that you enjoyed your treats. Thank you so much for the review and we look forward to seeing y’all again soon.

name: A Bomb
text: After visiting the lake for the last 6 years We finally have ice cream, or should I say custard!  And it’s delicious.  Our first visit was on July 1st and when we walked in we were immediately greeted with options and menus and a smiling deface by all.  Your right the sample of custard almost filled us up!   Had the turtle with salted sea caramel and the saltiness was perfect..  Stick around and keep churning!

resp.text: We're so glad that you had a good experience and that you enjoyed the Turtle Sundae.  We enjoyed meeting and making new friends over the holiday weekend. We look forward to seeing you again.

text:
Terrific new (and much needed) addition to Lake Martin. The frozen custard is excellent, topping choices are plentiful, everything is top quality and the owners are the bomb. We've been several times, tried several menu items and will definitely be returning to try others.
Parking can sometimes be slightly short (only at peak times) but is mostly available.
Strongly recommended.

resp.text: Thanks so much. We really appreciate y'all and look forward to your visits.

Baskins Robins  of Albertville is home of the couple of flavors if your lucky in a cup because they are also out of cones.. be glad you don't leave with a handful of unfrozen milk for 20 bucks. At this rate it won't last a year.

Friendly staff would definitely help too! I'll go back to try the waffles which seem interesting. Give it a try and definitely form your own opinion. Step up from the usual Brewsters if that helps any!

resp.text: Seretha, Thank you for leaving a review! We very much appreciate your kind words about our ice cream. At the same time, we are so sorry that our flavor selection did not exceed your expectations. Our goal each day is to provide above and beyond experiences for our guests through great products and service, and we do apologize that we were not able to do that in all categories. We hope you will be willing to give us another chance sometime soon. Michael G

resp.text: Paula, this has been brought to the attention of the management and was taken care of.  We apologize for anything being played that was offensive or inappropriate, these were never the intentions.  We hope you will give Sweet Charlie’s another opportunity to serve you and your family.  Michael G

Michael G

***LIMESTONE DRUG***
FRIENDLY STAFF

WONDERFUL STORE
THEY GOT WHAT YOU LOOKING FOR
AND WHEN YOU GO INSIDE LOOK TO YOUR RIGHT ON THE SHELF
EVERYTHING IS   $1.00 EACH

name: Richard Yard
text:
This pharmacy is the best! They will always fill a patient’s prescriptions! Unlike most pharmacies, you can get more than one prescription of the same pain killers by more than one doctor in the same week. Oh, and you can send friends to pick it up for you because they don’t believe in wasting one’s time w ID-ing. FINALLY, there’s a place out here in our beautiful, red, trump and god fearing city of Athens that just gets it, you know? Oh my gosh I haven’t even gotten to the best part about filling w this place...they deliver! Yes, even xanex. right to your door!
This place truly is a gem. They offer creatively overpriced (to some) children’s toys, scarfs, sodas, cigarettes and highly controlled substances at ease! If you’ve been bouncing around w your RXs and are worried about where to go, look no further! Get all of them filled here! Thanks limestone drug!

name: Joshua Southard
text: Limestone Drug always brings me back to my childhood just walking in seeing the old school ice cream and drink counter. But as pharmacies there are none that compare to the treatment of care and polite employees who are there to help you with your meds and talk to you about other things that are good for you. They treat every customer like it's was there family and has the ol country style of hospitality and helpful. 10 stars❗

name: Suzette Powers
text:
Great pharmacy and wonderful honest people. Super nice pharmacist very kind great honest people and kind sweet girls who take your script for the pharmacist to fill and they are very fast accurate. I'm 68 yrs old and I remember when the building Limestone Drugs is in wss a bank and I remember when Tom Dean moved the Soda Fountain over to the bank building from Gilbert's Drug Store and my parents and my brothers has been using Limestone Drug Store since it opened on the corner of the square in the old bank building. Great to have a company that's as old as Limestone Drugs.
Thanks S. Powers

text: Great pharmacy with great people. The pharmacists are very knowledgeable and friendly. Always willing to help in any way they can.

text: We are on vacation and chose this place for a quick light lunch. I am soooo happy we did. The owner and her partner were so friendly and attentive. Even discussed local things to do and entertainment. The food was amazing! I will definitely be coming back when I visit gulf shores again.

name: Richard Hart
text: Wonderful food and great service.  The pizza sub was probably the best I've ever had. All of our food was excellent.  Great bar selection.  The owners are wonderful people. We had great conversations. Definitely worth the visit.

name: Amanda Bartee
text: Love this little sweet beach bar!  We decided to try it out as we were staying at the Islands Winds West Condos and it was just a short walk across the road.  So glad we did!  Italian beef sandwich and the Pizza Sub were AMAZING!  Add a frozen sangria to the meal and it was perfect!  Definitely a must if you are down by the beach in Gulf Shores!  I would recommend this place over any of the bigger known establishments!  I wish the owner well! ❤️

name: Lindsey hotmessexpress
text: Best place in town! Amazing food. Good drinks! Gelato was the best. Owners are so personable and kind. Favorite place we went to on our trip, even over the beach!  Will come here every time we visit gulf shores.

name: Brandon Styles Live
text: Great simple menu and iced coffee. Will be back! Met the owner and her family, very sweet.

resp.text: Thanks so much Brandon and Diamond!! We loved meeting you and you family! See you guys soon!

name: Monica Lowe
text: Great wine, cheese, and atmosphere. Joey and Jordan are the sweetest and hard workers/ owners. Come here and enjoy everything!

name: Flavio Bruzzone
text: Really good food. Friendly and kind service.

name: Jennifer Hudson
text:
My husband and I stopped by “Lauria’s by the Beach”
for a quick date night. Both the service and the food was excellent! It was a nice change from the busy/fast paced side of Gulf Shores, and had a calm, welcoming, more cozy vibe. I would highly recommend and we definitely will be returning whenever we visit Gulf Shores!

name: Jeb Stuart
text: Can't say enough good things about this place. Honest humble proprietors doing a great job of providing fresh food and hospitality for anyone who walks in. Order anything and everything

name: Zac Coleman
text: GREAT spot. Cool story behind it and the owners have lots of passion behind it. Wine and cheese bar but in meantime a bagel and coffee shop! Excited to come back next time in town. Highly recommend. Right off the beach.

name: Jennifer Borage
text: Such a great place just across the street from the beach! The people who worked there were so friendly and seemed to put so much care into the food and the business. We had a blood orange sorbet mimosa, coffee afogado, a bottle of wine and a charcuterie board. Building our own board was fun, and it was so beautiful when it came out. We will definitely go back before our stay ends!

name: Alan Geetings
text:
We stumbled upon this place looking for a fun date spot. Wow!!  Super impressed by the young couple who are living out a dream by owning and running this cute spot. The wine was good, the charcuterie board was great, and the fogatto was amazing.

Try it out. You will love it. Local folks who work hard and care about what they do.

name: Dodge Cowart
text: I got food via Doordash and it was literally one of my favorite place to eat so far. Wonderful fresh sandwich and the tomato soup was sweet and perfect.

name: victoria gilmore
text: This is the cutest little place ever. Jordan was our bartender and was very outgoing. Made the experience great. I wish we would of found this place before our last day in Gulf Shores.

resp.text: Thank you Victoria! We are so excited to have our full bar. Safe travels!

name: Jonathan Smith
text: Extremely nice people. Great food and great prices as well will definitely be back when we visit next!

name: drgitzza
text: Beautiful story, great food, awesome people, intimate experience!

name: Jilly S
text: Love this new little gem! Not many coffee shops are open in the late afternoon, but Lauria’s was! They have a simple, yet fancy menu. We just got iced coffees, but will come back and try the Affogatos and the charcuterie boards!

name: Amanda Dykes
text: I love this place. Everything from Gelato to drinks to sandwiches has been wonderful.

name: KS B
text: Best Gelato, Best Bushwhacker made with Gelato, Best coffee and espresso our family had while in the area.  They also had a great meat and cheese charcuterie board.  We tried Bushwackers at all the main spots and Lauria's was by far the best.  This place is a great value and over the top good quality.  We went multiple times while we were in town and it was consistently good.  By choosing this business you will be supporting a true small family owned business.  They were super nice and made some great local restaurant recommendations which helped us get away from the super tourist traps.  Highly recommended.

name: Mike Gardner
text:
We LOVE this place...and the owner. Good coffee, bagels, service.
You will not be disappointed:-)

resp.text: We love you too! Thank you for stopping in, come and visit us again soon!

resp.text: Danielle we really appreciate you and you husband for stopping in and trying our charcuterie boards! Hope you see you both soon! We also have new cheeses every week!

text: I visited here today for the first time in a long time. I used to stop by here after high school for a Cranberry and White Chocolate scone, and wow are they just as delicious as I remember! This place is worth a stop. Very kind staff, I’ve never had a bad experience

name: Mallory Meriwether
text:
NEVER AGAIN! I just walked in there to get my 4 year old daughter one of their Signature Milkshakes that you see in the photo above. When we walked in they said that they were too busy make one of these milkshakes for my daughter. There were zero customers in the store.

My daughter left the store crying. They did not seem to care in the slightest. Don’t advertise something that you are too “busy” to make.

resp.text: Sorry we were not able to accommodate you.  We lost a day due to the storms and we were short staffed.  We were still preparing cupcakes and filling our cases as was stated.  I can't prepare a Milkshake without everything that is needed to go on it. Sorry for the inconvenience

name: Lauren Braxton
text: Everything tastes amazing, down to their homemade whipped cream! The milkshakes are out of this world, and you can’t beat their awesome customer service! Love Tee’s!

resp.text: Thank you so much for your review of our business.  Your opinion means so much to us.  So glad you enjoyed your shake,  and our customer service.  We hope to see you again soon.

name: Steven Jemison
text: Just heard of this place a few weeks ago, this was the second trip here!!! They have so many choices I just want one of every thing , had the mini strawberry cake last time wow!!!!! Tried the mini key lime pie this time, and a peanut butter brownie,  chocolate chip cookie and a toffee crunch cookie. After reading the other reviews I have to say the staff here was very friendly the two times I went in.

name: Red Stepchild
text:
** HUBBY got out of Trouble w/ Tee's Cupcakes. **
My Hubby forgot what day it was. In a panic, he visited Tea's and they SAVE HIS HEINNEY with a fabulous Glamorous cupcake that was so AMAZING that I couldn't believe he found these. As I type this review, my co-worker (another husband panicking "What do I but my wife for her birthday".. he is looking at Tea's website and drooling. A great lil gem of a place. Thank you from David & Stephany Henson.

name: Chad Beasley
text: We stopped by and got a few treats and everything I tried was amazing! The heath bar cookie and cherry danish were SOOOO good! I didn’t try the gigantic cupcakes but they looked incredible! They also have ice cream and over the top milkshakes. We will be back!

name: Darryl Peterson
text: I love this place!  I do not go as often as I like because I cannot afford the weight gain it would cause.  Everyone that has helped me has been wonderful.  I think there is a "feel" here that you find when the people truly love what they do.  The selection may be smaller than other bakeries, but that is what I expect for a small, hometown bakery - quality over quantity.  Even then, I'm sure that if I requested anything in advance I could get it.

name: Art 2 Leo
text: Customer service💯...Oreo cake👌🏾...Peanut butter cake/cupcakes 🏁...and MUCH MORE. I was impressed upon arrival, witnessing one of the owners assist a customer to the car, with a beautifully decorated cake. GREAT PLACE.I’d give them 6 stars..

name: Joey Williams
text: Tried to order a Birthday cake for my daughter, was flat out told they could not get to it even with several days advance notice.  I have been faithful to this company since the first day they opened, but would not buy another thing from them, nor recommend them to anyone.

resp.text: Hello Joey thank you for your review. You just called about 30 minutes ago, if I'm not mistaken,  and asked the owner for a cake tomorrow(not advanced notice). We were more than happy to get you a traditional cake,  but you were wanting a custom designed cake.  I am completely booked on any custom cakes.  I try my absolute hardest to squeeze in as many last minute orders as I possibly can,  but I have a limit and there are people who order weeks and months in advance and I must honor their orders first.  I do apologize that we were not able to accommodate your request.

name: Greg Mattes
text: Order a custom cake, yellow cake with fudge filling and chocolate buttercream for my wife’s b-day. She said it is one of the best cakes she has had. Cake was moist, fudge filling was awesome and the chocolate buttercream was not to sweet but had lots of flavor. Lots of other desserts and pastries to try here. She is waiting for the next occasion so we can order another cake. They were very good at getting this cake for me as it was on short notice a little over a day. Thank you!

name: Scott Wheeler
text: Great place with great food and great people. They stayed open almost an hour late just so my girlfriend and I could meet up from different parts of the state and eat there. Cheap and delicious, will definitely return

resp.text: Thank you very much for stopping by.  So glad you enjoyed your experience and sweets with us.  See  you soon.

name: Lexx Slays
text: This place is absolutely amazing!!!!! Clean,  friendly,  welcoming atmosphere.  The pastries and sweets are to die for!!!! Not only are the cakes and pastries beautifully decorated they also taste amazing.  The absolute BEST place in town!!! If you haven't been GO!!!!

resp.text: Thank you so much for reviewing Teescakes&pastries. So glad that you enjoyed your experience with us.  Looking forward to seeing you again

name: Kala Patterson
text: Very rude & poor customer service !!!

resp.text: Hello Kayy. I'm sorry you feel you had a bad experience. You left a bad review because we were not able to produce a custom cake with an extremely short notice.  You called first did not have a guest count, cake design, nor a photo of what you wanted and expected a price.  You then sent a photo late Thursday evening via Facebook after  closing hours and needed the cake produced on saturday.  I simply told you no that I was booked. Please learn proper etiquette when inquiring services. We were not being rude , we were trying to get further information from you.  Be blessed.

From a birthday cake milkshake topped with donuts, to a pickle flavored shaved ice (you guessed it, a pickle is included). Take your kids, grandkids, nieces and nephews because The Sugar Shack is open only during the spring and summer. You don't wanna miss your chance to experience what they have to offer.

Our hours on posted on the lighted sign by the front door at The Sugar Shack and also on our Sugar Shack  Facebook page. name: Stephanie G
text: Okay so this might be a long  review.... the Reuben is delicious.   They slice their own meat (amazing).  Try the Italian or the Cuban also (can't decide which one is my favorite).  They are so much more than an ice cream shop!  The wings are delicious,  so many flavors to choose from(many more options than are posted on the big board).  Haven't had the pizza but the cheezy bread is so good! They have homemade  chili!!!!! Milkshakes are the bomb!  The owners have been all over and they definitely know how to cook!   Friendly people who like to take care of their customers.  Pet friendly as well.  Will update soon with pics!

text: They have really good pizzas.  I've tried the various meat and the mediterranean pizzas.  Their traditional and boneless wings are awesome.  I've tried their buffalo and lemon pepper flavors.  Love the milk shakes.  They have great staff and they always give pleasant service.  They can handle large orders and are very accommodating.  Game nights always include pizza and wings from The Country Cone.

text: So we walk in at 8:55pm. They have already covered all ice cream and cookies. The manager is counting down the drawer. He asked can I help you (he should have said we are closed) and I told him 1 scoop of cotton candy ski jump. He quickly said I have already closed the ice cream. So bacisly, they are closed at 8:55pm. If the door is unlocked, wouldn't you believe they are opened? Very Rude. Couldnt care less a paying customer was there.  Won't spend my money or time here ever again. This is the new normal in America. His business must be one that is NOT struggling!!! Good Luck to you!!!

resp.text: We are so sad to hear that you had a less than 5-star experience! Please contact our customer service team at customerservice@gfgmanagement.com, referencing this review.

name: L Cannon
text: I AM NEVER GOING BACK TO THIS PLACE!!!! The manager needs some very important training on customer service. My son and I was here yesterday. The cashier got the order wrong. She called my son a liar after he explained that the order was wrong. She said she can’t take my son’s word over her employee and he should respect that. No you should respect that your rude behavior is costing you customers. It took everything in me not to respond like you. Even the customer you were helping decided to take a pic of his order request because of my experience. That says a lot. Sometimes a little kindness goes a long way instead you lost a customer because of your rude behavior.

resp.text: We are so sad to hear that you had a less than 5-star experience! Please contact our customer service team at customerservice@gfgmanagement.com and let us know what happened.

I asked for the manager and she claimed to be the manager so I left. I didn’t want to drive out to the Galleria today, but I ended up doing it and that location took cake of my cake.

resp.text: We are so sad to hear that you had a less than 5-star experience! Please contact our customer service team at customerservice@gfgmanagement.com and let us know what happened.

resp.text: Thank you for the 5 stars, Geneva! We appreciate you.

name: michael c
text: My wife and son were treated horribly here. Employee gave my son the wrong order, told him he could not return the cookies because of COVID-19. The store manager told my son that it was his word against the employee’s and he would just have to respect that. So after basically calling my son a liar my wife goes in and the same store manager lies and says she didn’t say this to my son and attempts to chastise my wife about how my son was wrong. Mind you, the employee that got the order wrong  just stands there and allows my son to take the blame for his mistake, he says nothing. Long story short, my wife wasn’t having it she threw the wrong order in the trash at the store, the store manager still had to give her the correct order and we will never purchase anything from there again.

resp.text: Michael, we are so sad to hear that you had a less than 5-star experience! Please contact our customer service team at customerservice@gfgmanagement.com referencing this review and let us know what happened.

resp.text: We are so sad to hear that you had a less than 5-star experience! Please contact our customer service team at customerservice@gfgmanagement.com and let us know what happened.

resp.text: KandkR, we are so sad to hear that you had less than a 5 star experience! Please know that we have informed the franchise owner due to the fact that each location is independently owned and operated!

name: Jasmine Pettaway Kemp REALTOR
text: This was my third trip and it was good as always. Service was quick and the employees were polite and suggested great combinations. The employees were following COVID-19 protocol and the store front was marked accordingly. I’ve cream was packaged to-go and stayed cold and composed the entire 20 minute ride home.

name: Rachel Leyva
text: Workers had masks below nose, seemed annoyed that I had questions about mix ins, and I stood in front of the checkout counter while two ladies stood behind the counter chatting. One was texting on her phone with her gloves on. When one worker finally realized I was waiting to check out, she told the other employee “she’s been standing here to check out and you on your phone” to which the other employee replied “I’m not at work right now.” The girl said “You’ve been saying that all day”. How is this acceptable behavior?  This is my second time coming to this location and it has been HORRIBLE both times. Don’t waste your time here. You will be so mad after leaving that you won’t even taste the sub-par ice cream. Total time in store getting a cup of ice cream? 15 MINUTES. And no other customers were getting ice cream.

name: George Davis
text: Horrible experience. Workers all had masked below nose or below chin, no distancing between the workers, orders were wrong after clearly stating them multiple times, ice cream was melted, and way over priced. Ice cream was just not good either. I loved Maggie Moo's, and I've been there numerous times in the northeast. However, this was not the standard I remembered. Will not be back

name: rebekah lusk
text: Terrible service. None of the employees knew answers about the menu, menu wasn’t even showing on the TV, and no one made any effort to tell me menu options even after asking multiple times. Did not even end up getting what I ordered, even though I repeated it. When I pointed out that the order was wrong, the worker was rude to me I typically love marble slab and will put up with the price for good ice cream and service, but certainly never coming back to this location.

name: shivangi khandekar
text: Love the place! Superfriendly staff! I love their birthday cake and dark chocolate icecreams! Keep it up!!

name: Erin Shockey
text:
I wish i could give Dreamcakes Cafe a million star review! Wow! I visited Dreamcakes Cafe with my mother and sister for afternoon tea. It was such a special day for us because we planned afternoon tea right before they accompanied me to shop for my wedding dress! The staff knew this and were so excited, kind, and encouraging.

We made our tea selections a few days before our event via email. Kallie was wonderful about responding on email. We had to sign a contract prior to the tea and she made it very easy to do so. When we arrived to the cafe, our tea table was set up with everything we needed: teacups, utensils, saucers, even fresh flowers! The set up was stunning and the food was delicious! I highly recommend the pimento cheese sandwich with peach jam and the macarons!!

During the tea, the wait staff made us feel so special. Someone was always by to ensure we had everything we needed, refill cups, etc and all of them were SO polite, friendly, and knowledgable about tea selections. My sister had a gluten and dairy allergy and they made sure she knew what she could and couldn't eat and even brought out a special cup of chicken salad for her.

Thank you Dreamcakes staff! You made this such a special day for us. The thought and time you put into the details of our tea was noticed and SO appreciated. It was perfect from start to finish. Hope to see yall again soon... we will be back!!

resp.text:
Thank you so much Erin! It was such a pleasure working with you. We really enjoyed serving you during your tea and are so happy that you enjoyed it so much! We are pleased to accommodate all allergies and love that we were able to find the best solution for your sister. We love going above and beyond for you customers! We look forward to seeing you in the future!

- Dreamcakes Cafe Staff

name: Kathy McLaurin

However, I loved the other flavors provided! My advice: don’t get the vanilla, and make sure you check to make sure you pay for the cupcakes you actually want! text: Not a good experience. The pulled pork from The Smoke was flavorless. Macaroni and cheese was not much better. The burrito place and the sandwich truck were closed because of social distancing, but all that did was congregate everyone to one spot at the BBQ truck, so it had a complete adverse effect. The Chill truck had terrible margaritas for $14 a pop. Kids loved it though! The live music was good and it was a fun hang. DO NOT go for the food. We picked that location because of the open seating, social distanced set up. We ate and ran. Steer clear. Maybe when life gets back to normal and they have more options this locale will be worth a visit.

Hi Barbara! Thank you for taking time to leave your thoughts;  we appreciate your positive feedback ~ our team works to keep wait time short, environment clean, and flavors fresh & varied.
In addition to seating, we also like to remind customers we have a drive-thru option too :)
Please pop by again soon ~ we look  forward to serving you fresh, frozen fun!

text: I paid $6 for a small chocolate coffee shake and it tasted like a workout drink. Definitely water based with no milk. It tasted absolutely nothing like coffee at all and was very bland. Save your money and get Arby's.

resp.text:
Hi Sean. We agree - Arby's has a great shake.

And, you're correct! We do not have dairy-based protein smoothies; we have coconut milk sweetened with Stevia as "magic milk" base.  We use Ghirardelli chocolate powder & Ghirardelli syrup. Our mocha powder has 20g protein/scoop.

We certainly would have made you another option (probably recommending no protein powder). Hopefully there's something else you'd like to try - maybe a delicious pop? Our Cold Brew is a popular coffee-flavored pop. Next time you're downtown,  please introduce yourself to Pop Guy!

Thanks for taking time to provide your feedback. We value your opinion 🙂

We topped ours with condensed milk or caramel and all was yummy! Super great atmosphere too! Worth the trip if you're debating getting ice cream here, try it! text: This was my first time trying Insomnia Cookies and I must say I was impressed. The 2 ladies at the counter greeted and assisted me. I originally came for white chocolate macadamia nut cookies,  but they were out. The cookies I did get were  fresh, warm, and really good. They also serve ice cream here. I highly recommend this place.

name: Gavin Dunn
text: Gotta be honest I’ve been to many insomnias and never had cookies be hard and stale. The cookies here were hard and tasted like they’d sat out a while. I would probably skip this location.

name: AleishaDavisDesigns TheSableBelle
text:
Very inconsiderate customer service... almost rude. Inability to supply the flavor demand for 24ct cookies on multiple occasions and THIS is a menu item! Our family requested four six count flavors, and neither of the four flavors were available at quantities of six. The frail pale girl tries to force you to substitute... or even order fewer cookies. This has me completely baffled because she would rather loose money than provide service.
While the cookies are fantastic, I often wondered why no one has ever said "there will be a five minute wait on those" or "we'll have to bake them for you"...a cookie takes less than fifteen minutes to bake...and you ARE serving them warm...I'm beginning to wonder what the big picture behind this cookie place really is when you can't accommodate a customer at three o'clock in the afternoon. I can't imagine that they will be in business long-term.  Customer service goes a LONG way... not to mention the business practice is a bit sketchy.

name: Bille Miller
text:
Let me tell you something. I've eaten a lot of cookies in my lifetime, but these are the best cookies ever.
Our cookies were still warm and fresh. Crispy outside with a warm chewy center.
Hands down, the best cookies I've had in a long time.
Definitely will be going back.

name: Foodie chick
text: great young lady with bun in hair who worked the front Sunday morning! very polite and had great customer service experience from her! really helped us choose are cookies as this was are first time. cookies were warm and delicious!  the place was very clean and smelt great. overall 5 out of 5!

name: Toya
text: I ordered twice online. Both times the cookies were warm, fresh, and delicious. My order was a bit hard to track because they have their own delivery drivers. So, when grubhub called to check on the order status,  no one answered the phone. I still received my cookies on time though.

name: Brandon Dennis
text: I have to say that experience was all 5 stars and good. Honestly after a couple of minutes I was really wanting some cookies so I go to check and see where they are it still says baking the next thing I know is I'm getting a knock on the door. In the .5 seconds it took me to get up and check the door the possible supper human maybe Jesse Owen's delivery driver dropped the cookies at the door knocked and booked it back to the car, took off faster then the flash on a good day and was gone. I have to say keep up the good work and my next question is do they get paid by the delivery because that driver is all aces in my book now..

name: Priscilla Diaz
text: If it was possible to give this place a ZERO star rating I definitely would. Rude Customer service, the lady who was up front short brown hair was not wearing a mask- so I assumed I didn’t have to either. She proceeded to be rude over any question that I had, in the mist of it all she says “oh by the way you need to wear a mask”. When she wasn’t wearing hers? Loud Chatter I get it it’s not so busy- but a customer should never have to hear conversations. It will be my first and last time ever going in. I was looking forward to it but I will not waste my time nor my money to a business who hires horrible employees that cannot handle to fake it until they make it!

name: David Nguyen
text: Always have the best service here and the most delicious cookies!!! The monsterwich is no joke.

name: kjkk2
text: Cookies are good but I waited an hour after they said my order would be ready at 3:00. I have no problem waiting but if you are backed up just say so and give a new pickup time rather than having someone sit in their car for an hour.

name: Jen Anderson
text:
I’ve been really excited to try this place because I’ve heard so much hype about the insomnias in other places, but it was honestly a let down. They don’t take cash at all for some reason, which is ridiculous. The guy behind the counter was cool, it’s not his fault or anything, they’re just out of stock of every good cookie, and although the cookies are good, they’re not $2.00 a cookie good, especially for the size. The ice cream was okay, not bad but not amazing (you can probably find the exact same ice cream at the grocery store) but the guy did fill up the container the proper amount.
TLDR: counter dude is cool, it’s just expensive and overhyped

name: Marty Irvin
text: Don't waste your time. High price and won't get order right. PLUS WILL NOT TAKE CASH

name: Bambi Diaz
text: I'm no one to complain, but if I'm required to wear a mask coming in along with other customers, the employees must wear mask as well instead being RUDE to a couple who didn't have a mask! This short brown hair lady told a customer to put on a mask in a rude way, yet this employee didn't have one herself! If she's good to be rude and tell customers what to do, she should be good enough to wear a mask herself!

name: CeeMuh Official
text: I've ordered multiple times in the last few weeks. Customer service hasn't been a problem for me, I always order in the late evening. However, the cookies are hit or miss. The first time I ordered I had warm, soft vegan cookies. I have not had it like that since then. I only get the vegan cookies. So a few times they have been super hard and tasted like they had been left out for awhile. I started telling them to please make them fresh when ordering online. It just sucks I have to specify every time just to make sure they're not rock hard.

name: Lillian-Lotus Buccola
text: Night staff is AMAZING and cookies are my new crack lol

name: Joseph Puckett
text: I think these are the best cookies in town. Fast food cookies taste like garbage to me now. I was actually surprised to see this place rated so low. I've never met anyone rude here.

text: Good cookies. Open late.

name: Juan Diaz
text: Rude customer service. Girl was rude and didn't seem to want to make sell. Asked a question about the cookie because it was my first in there and she was rude about need people that are willing to help people not be rude to them.

name: Amber S
text: There should be an option for -stars.  We have been looking forward to trying this new place. Upon arriving , it was odd to get in & dirty. We weren’t greeted pleasantly & the people before us had been waiting awhile. They were out of most items. When asked about a certain cookie , we were told it would be about 20 min. Please tell me who has this time to wait on grab & go items? As I pondered on whether to order or not, I decided this place doesn’t deserve my business. This place will not be in business long! It’s gross because it doesn’t look or feel clean. It’s right beside a hair/nail salon, so the smells don’t mix well. Customer service is horrible & the presentation of the items looked horrible. Stay away!

name: Margaret Mathews
text: So, I was aware of this place with supposedly great cookies and was debating on trying it. I can certainly afford the product, but they ARE a bit pricey. Now, I’m reading these negative reviews regarding awful customer service. Where is the owner and why are they not personally responding to each and every one of the complaints? The common denominator is obviously the individual with the attitude who hasn’t been properly trained, has no people skills and apparently, isn’t concerned about losing her job.  I’m not going to give you my hard earned money to come into your establishment to be bullied and insulted. Keep your overpriced cookies and good luck trying to make it in Mobile with that level of counter help.

name: Tammy Crook
text: Room temp cookies and my "pint of ice cream was 3 scoops. I won't be back.

name: Katelyn Cowie
text: I’ve been to insomnia cookies several times. I’ve been a fan for several years every since I have been to the location in my hometown in Birmingham.  I went to the Mobile location today that just opened and the cashier lady that made my cookiewich literally pressed her whole hand down on the ice cream sandwich to squish it down. She was NOT wearing gloves. The cookies are good, but I hope they better train the employees on this kind of issue.

name: Morgan G
text: Unfortunately, my negative review is due to the short female with dark hair who works up front, which seems to be a common theme according to other reviews. My husband and I had a very unpleasant interaction with her in which she told us "yall have to look at the menu before coming in here. You people are holding up the line and taking forever because you don't know what you want when you come in". Granted, we were still standing outside of the shop when she said this. Even the people behind us commented on how rude she was. When I asked her where the menu was, she pointed at a paper that was hanging on the door (that was folded in half) and said "LOOK AT THE PAPER" which showed the website. If we hadn't already waited for a while, we would have left. That girl is rude and terrible at her job. Everyone else was pleasant and we received our order quickly. However, we will not go back because of that woman. She ruined the whole thing for us.

name: Alex J
text: Horrible service no one answers phone took 2 hours to get cookies and ice cream. We spent 62.00 here they should definitely have awesome service for prices.

text: I'm giving this establishment 2 stars because the customer service is horrible! How could a restaurant so new to the area already have employees that act as though they HATE their job!?? The cookies are very delicious, but the customer services makes me not want to spend my money there at all! Also, prices are a little bit high..which I really wouldn't mind so much if the cashiers weren't so rude and nonchalant. Work on your customer service before you charge an arm and a leg for cookies and milk!

text:
Lupitas has the best ice cream I’ve ever tasted! I’m not usually a fan of ice cream but I’m a fan of Lupitas! It was so fresh, creamy, and full of flavor (I got caramel). The young lady serving us welcomed us with a genuine smile and offered samples. I was very impressed!

The building was a bit hard to find on Apple Maps, but it’s in the shopping center with a furniture store. It could use some renovations but honestly the quality, price, and customer service will override cosmetics. It was also very clean inside and smelled clean!

I will definitely be going back whenever I’m in the city. This is a small town hidden gem you don’t want to miss!

name: Donna G.
text: My family and I went here to eat last weekend and we loved it. It's inside the cutest building, with the upstairs done in retro checkered floors and red seating.  The windows are huge and you can see right out to the square. The best part is the square is all done up for Christmas and it's absolutely breathtaking looking down from the windows. The food was really good I ordered the Southwestern Chicken Wrap and ate every bite of it. The service is great and the staff are super friendly. If you're in Andalusia it's definitely a place to stop by and grab a bite to eat.

name: Tina Roberts

My daughter who does usually talk to people she doesn’t know always leaves talking to them.  So very friendly and helpful. I’d give 5 stars and 2 thumbs up!! Oh... and we are about to be on our way now. 😊

I Love this place! I've eaten lunch here twice
Had a French dip with Au Jus and, it was fresh, hot and, delicious. The service was quick and staff was friendly. Looking forward to going back.

name: Shirley Watson
text: Picked up an ice cream cake. Really needed an afternoon coffee and they made a fresh pot. We had ice cream then and will enjoy the cake later. Lovely service and delicious treats. What could be better.

name: Thomas Moore
text: You know that pre-cut cubed chicken you can get at Walmart to add to salads? Microwave it under a wet paper towel so it loses its texture and gives it the color of canned tuna. This appears to be the recipe for the chicken used in their chicken-based wraps. Lost your teeth in a motorcycle accident on the way here? Forgot your dentures at home? This is the place for you. I'm hoping this is an anomaly. Maybe their supplier ran out of chicken. Didn't try the ice cream  this time, hope it's still good!

name: Taylor Miller
text: Tried it for the first time yesterday. I loved the NY Cheesecake ice cream. Not crazy about the chocolate dipped waffle cone or the wraps. If you get a waffle cone be prepared for it to drip out of the bottom a lot. Other than that, everything else was great.

name: Charles Walden
text: Wow, where do I start with The Spot 4°? It is a quaint little ice cream shop nuzzled in a small shopping area off of Rainbow Drive.. when they are actually open. Beware: if you want rolled ice cream, you HAVE to call prior to making a trip there. Myself, along with others I know, have made trips for the roll ice cream delicacy just for them to not be open.. might I add, with their refined COVID-19 hours. It is great to be open over the weekend, however I thought they were supposed to open on January 8th, 2021 after being closed since late November- early December? It is kinda dumbfounding to be closed over Christmas break when most everyone is off of work, kids are out of school, and people are out shopping. Now, COVID-19 has hit businesses hard, but it shouldn’t be an excuse after excuse for your misconceptions. If you haven’t been opened in sooo long, what are you guys doing with the financial reprieves in which come as relief packs due to COVID-19? I’m starting to think you all have forgotten you own an ice cream business. These people, not exactly sure who is responding to reviews, but for every complaint or substandard review, there is a clap-back. No apologies for what they have done, if there was an error, etc. What a bad way to do business! There are key attributes you never do as a business. The customer may not always be correct, but they think they are in their reality. It is CRITICAL to never disagree with the customer, as this makes them angry and argumentative. It’s not in anyone’s best interest to call a customer out for being wrong, don’t focus on the negative.. just like you people are doing. It is very important to establish interpersonal relationships by being business owners with your customers. However, the prices for ONE roll or milkshake are okay-ish, but you could still blow out an entire paycheck on a family outing for ice cream. They have clap-backed for their lack of hours claiming they do not have enough money to pay employees to stand around. Now, I may be wrong here, but I am pretty sure this is a family-owned, local business. The only people I have ever seen working are the owners and their daughter. So how does it account for “we CAN’T afford to pay employees to sit around all day everyday with no customers coming in”? I think it’s the laziness of these business owners to not feel like running their business. From what it sounds like, business used to be booming. But they, over time, have significantly cut their hours more and more down, they do not engage the public (in Facebook posts) like they used to, they used to have specials & giveaways, and they were more prominent overall. I understand COVID-19 affects everyone differently (and while you might have had exposure,) it shouldn’t be 2 months worth of not opening. Let me save everyone some time: there is no telling when this shop will open, if they ever open again. I have a hack to share with you guys! To save time AND money, simply google a rolled ice cream recipe. You are able to find countless recipes on Pinterest or by googling how to make it. You are to mix together, or blend, the add ins of your choice, mixed with heavy cream and sweetened condensed milk. If you order any kind of special rolls from this place, be sure to note what all is in them. Pour the mixed up/ blended mixture out on a baking sheet and stick into the freezer for a few hours; from here, you can cut strips into the flattened, frozen mixture. You can then roll it up with a spatula. This is guaranteed to save you more time and money rather than dealing with unreliable, fickle small spot shop this one happens to be. I am ready for you to respond to me, you guys have nothing on me or the success I protrude. I hope you guys learn one day, how to build relationships with customers, how to be reliable in your words, and how to properly run a successful business before you guys close for good!

name: Weird Guy
text: Let me start by saying the PRICES ARE ABSOLUTELY OUTRAGEOUS. No way a family of 4 much less 5 or more could come in and get a treat w/o spending $50 plus. Also the rolled ice cream is nothing but tastless frozen cream. I ordered the strawberry and they put ( I swear to it ) a half of 1 strawberry in the cream and chopped it up to where the cream would have a pink color to it. Its absolutely tasteless. They put MAYBE 3 or 4 oz of cream on the table and roll it and charge for some over 8 dollars. I think mine with the half strawberry and nuts was 9 dollars. My son ordered a rolled fruity pepple with strawberry pop tart and they put a half of a plastic TEASPOON of fruity pepples and maybe 1/4 of a pop tart in it. I understand a business has to make money as I own my own business as well. But I also know that u have to be fair and give customers what they paid for. This is almost like robbery. Lol. Seriously. I was in there when a dad let his 4 children order then his wife , then himself and the total was 78 dollars. That was him and his wife and 3 children. His jaw about hit the floor. I know mine did. So many other GREAT chooses that give MORE for your money and the prices are literally half of what this place charges. As far as the staff they are great. But not so great that i would choose to go here and spend MORE money than i would at another local ice cream shop.

resp.text:
Dear unsatisfied customer in every way,

Thank you so much for your feedback. We value every customers opinion although we can’t please everyone. I do find it very strange that within a hour of you making this review you also gave another bad review to another local ice cream shop... As far as your $9 strawberry roll with nuts is concerned, that is NOT CORRECT. A basic roll is $6.00 plus .50 per topping. Which would make your total $7 plus tax. With strawberry rolls you get FRESH strawberries on the inside and on top, we also add strawberry syrup unless requested other wise so I’m not for sure how your rolls came out tasteless with just a little pink tint.As far as the amount of “cream” that goes on the table it makes 6 rolls and fills up a 12 oz cup.. Also our rolls are $6 not $8-$9 unless you add 4-6 topping..
To address the  1/2 of plastic teaspoon of fruity pebbles in a roll that is DEFINITELY NOT CORRECT. It’s not even possible to put 1/2 of a spoon. We actually put 2 full spoons. I mean it is a roll not a bowl of cereal. To address the pop tart issue we do have to spread and roll the ice cream (not sure if you’ve ever tried to do it) but it would be IMPOSSIBLE to roll with a entire pop tart inside. We do add pop tart on top as well JUST LIKE we do the strawberries. We use fresh fruits and good quality products at our store. We have people literally drive from all over for our ice cream and LOVE IT! We have several REPEAT Customers the come every week and sometimes even twice a week. But You’re always welcome to address any concerns you have directly to us at our store location or of course leave a review like you chose to do. Hopefully you can find somewhere that can satisfy your every need as a business and you don’t see any jaw dropping when hearing a price...
So we do apologize “Mr. Weird Guy”
With you being a business owner as you say in your review I’m quite shocked at how many compliments you have on line but didn’t express any concern in the store. As every business owner knows we appreciate the chance to correct the problem before going on line leaving a review that clearly has nothing good to say other than we have good staff! Although I do appreciate that. Hopefully if I ever visit your business whatever it may be my review will be much more satisfying ❤️
Be blessed and have a awesome day!
P.S as far as our prices being “almost robbery SERIOUSLY”
We actually give back to our community more than you can imagine and we do this for FREE. We get some jaw dropping from that as well 😀

text:
I’ve been to this location multiple times never having a great experience but the last visit was the last time I’ll give my business to this location.
The girl working was not kind or helpful. I asked for the custard which she said “we are out.” Totally get that- but it’s what I came in for so I asked when it would be ready to serve which she came back with “I don’t know... not today though.” It was barely early afternoon.
I then asked about flavors in the case- which she said “honestly I don’t know what flavor it is- I would have to text my manager.” Not the most encouraging statement. I asked a few more questions but I could tell she was annoyed by my questions, so I picked a flavor quickly to just be done.
When she handed me the cup the custard was already melting over the sides- while I appreciated the generous helping, she stood and watched me as I cleaned up the mess she gave me along with what fell on the counter. No help or offer to help- just watching me struggle.
As a paying customer, I do expect to have some sort of kindness and helpfulness when I am giving you my business. I understand that it is “only $5 worth of custard” but some level of customer service instead of treating someone as an burden will get you a long way. I truly hope this location steps up on there employee training as this is not my first bad experience.

text: Was downtown and decided to swing in for a deluxe chicken salad sandwich. That's a really tasty Chicken Salad with bacon and lettuce, it was great. You can also get almost any sandwich in a cone. I know sounds crazy , that is until your try it, then you realize it's crazy delicious, especially the aforementioned chicken salad. Don't forget a side of potato salad like none you have had before. Then for dessert you can get an ice cream cone with a fresh waffle cone made right before your eyes. Imagine a waffle cone with cookies and cream and the cone is still warm. Now if you like REAL southern sweet tea, this is the place. i don't even think that Brett (the owner) realizes what great sweet tea he makes. Much better than other restaurants I've been to. The point is that if you haven't been downtown on foster street during lunch, be sure to go soon and check out Stix and Cones. You can thank me later.

name: John Oliver
text:
My friends and I stumbled upon this place by chance on a day trip to Columbus. At first glance, it’s a quaint, clean, cool little ice cream shop. However, in a quick conversation with the owners, my friends learned that they also offered Indian cuisine and they were offered a free sample. Intrigued, But unable to eat there that day, we all decided to make a special trip to try to the food the following week.

We could not have made a better decision, as this was some of the best food I have ever had. The abundance of flavor was just what I was hoping for and the quality was almost like having a homemade meal served at your table. The owners (it’s a family operated business) checked on us and seemed very genuinely interested in our experience. They were extremely hospitable and friendly, making great conversation and adding to the experience with a very personal touch.

Ice Queen is well worth the time and I’m looking forward to going back!

name: Corey Moore
text: This place is a hidden jem. My wife and I wanted ice cream so we stopped randomly here to find they offer a full authentic Indian menu. We came back this weekend to try their food and it was beyond incredible. Gluten free friendly and vegetarian friendly, which is perfect for my wife and I. We'll travel from Albany for this every chance we get from now on. Could not recommend enough.

text: Really enjoyed having rolling ice cream here. Probably, the best ice cream I have ever had. The staff is very welcoming and provides good hospitality. I would highly suggest this place.

name: Lucy Clarke
text: Everything there is delicious. I had the tandoori chicken bowl and samosa as my meal, and it was great. Their coconut milk tea was very refreshing, too. The rolled ice cream was excellent, all of the flavors were very good. Everyone working there was super nice and helpful, and they even gave us an extra samosa to apologize for any extra wait time. I would definitely recommend coming here for dessert or dinner (or both).

resp.text: Thank You for your kind review Lucy! We can’t wait to serve you guys again!

name: Radon Vex
text: My wife and I use to come here only for bubba tea. Today, we decided to try their food and it was better than I expected. I got a matcha tea and I hated so the guy made me a Tara tea free of charge. It was absolutely delicious. Ice queen truly deserves 5 stars. The staff is extremely nice the place is always clean. They work quickly and the prices aren’t to bad either. Definitely a hidden gem in Columbus.

name: Amber
text: Been there three times in the past month. I love the boba, especially the brown sugar boba. And I love the honeydew milk tea and the chai milk tea.  The staff was super friendly and helpful. The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is because when we got the popping boba, a lot of them were already popped so we were just getting the empty boba shells. Besides that, this place is awesome! I definitely recommend going

name: Megan Phillips
text: PHENOMENAL traditional Indian food. Yes, the ice cream is great too, but we drive all the way from Albany for the Indian food. The Chicken 65 is incredible. I can’t have gluten and the owner’s mother is so sweet and guides me on what I can order. We are addicted.

name: Jessie Daniel
text: Great service and yummy food :) respectfully 💕

name: Vivian 'Valkyrie' Piorkowski
text: Our first time and I want to go back. Thankfully it's not far from my house. My sons really enjoyed being able to watch them and they thought it was just amazing how it turned from liquid to ice cream. The variety of ice cream flavors and toppings is great. My husband got a philly cheesesteaks and he said it was really good.

name: Amber

text: Had a spicy tandoori wrap and fries.  So delicious!!!

name: lydicake yumyum
text: My husband heard about it through a coworker, so we decided to give it a try. When I tell you we weren't disappointed about our trip here. We chose make your own ice cream bowl. It was so delicious, and I love the strawberry pop. The strawberry pop is little squeeshy balls that burst in your mouth, and they are excellent

resp.text: Lydicake! Thank you so much for your review! We are glad we were able to meet your expectations and deliver a great product! We can’t wait to share more exciting items with you soon! PS: Strawberry Pop’s are our absolute favorite too!

name: Daniyal Gaziani
text: Really enjoyed having rolling ice cream here. Probably, the best ice cream I have ever had. The staff is very welcoming and provides good hospitality. I would highly suggest this place.

name: Michael Lynch
text: Novelty way to prepare your ice cream. Watching them prepare your treat is a treat. The post it wall is a great idea.

name: Benjamin Poteat
text: Definitely a nice place to go for dessert, even during quarantine. They wear masks and prepare your treat safely, as always, and are very nice! Definitely recommend to anyone looking to get a tasty treat for a decent price!

resp.text: Thank You for your kind review Benjamin! Yes! Safety of our customers and crew is of the utmost importance to us! We can’t wait to see you guys again soon!

name: Breanna Swain
text: Really Vegan friendly and good food

name: Ben Butler
text: good food ,great fresh ice cream ,great and polite staff

name: Jewel Patterson
text: This is INCREDIBLE food. Go try it, you will NOT be disappointed!!! The ice cream and drinks are also fantastic, but really really go for the food.

resp.text: Thank You for your kind review Jewel! We can’t wait to serve you again! PS: We have added an expanded menu since your last visit 😉 come check out more of delicious items we have to offer!!

name: Titian Dahlvang
text: Great little shop for rolled icecream and Indian food! It's all halal by the way! Great service, and great product. Family run little joint. Best things to get in my opinion are Taro Bubble Tea, Morning Call rolled icecream, and Chicken 65!

resp.text: Thank You for your review Titian! Come see us sometime with Nadia!

name: Zachary Stine
text: Best ice cream in Columbus!  Quite a spectacular process to watch them roll the ice cream on a cold table. Tastes as good as it looks!

name: Angel

name: Luke Miller

resp.text: Thank You so much Luke. We are so glad you enjoyed your visit! Can’t wait to serve you again soon!

name: A M
text: I have been her twice. I love their bubble tea and the bowls. The food is great and is prepared quickly.

resp.text: Thank You for your kind review AM!

name: Angela Graves
text: Didn’t even know this restaurant was back here. We stopped in to try, what a great find. Food was fresh and delicious, will be back again.

resp.text: Thank You Angela! We can’t wait to see you again!

text: The ice cream rolls are good and getting to watch them make them is an experience in itself.

As fun to watch being made as it is to eat.
Edit: RIP Royal Cafe, long live Ice Queen.

name: Red2Gaming
text: I dont generally leave reviews unless the place is bad but this place is by far my favorite ice cream place ever I 10/10 recommend here worth the wait time if there is a wait

resp.text: Thank You so much for taking the time to leave us a feedback! We are so glad to be your favorite icecream place! We are trying very hard to rectify the wait times without sacrificing quality or the signature homemade taste that our customers love!

name: Tylor Hall
text: My first time, and didn't disappoint.  I'm a kid at heart, so I got the fruity pebbles.  Staff was very friendly with greeting when entering and exiting.  Highly recommend.

name: Victor Craven
text: This place is 100% 🔥, go in or get their food delivery. The fruit tea is delicious everytime! #IndianFood #BobaTea

resp.text: Thank you for your kind review Victor! We strive hard to be 100%🔥 for our customers!

name: erc royals
text:
I have been to 2 other rolled ice cream places and this was bad.  After we ate the ice cream we had a faty oil residue all over the inside of our mouth it was gross.  The workers were very nice.  However they need to wash the curtain to the back room it was very dirty looking.

Updated response to ice queen response:

If you use fresh then you wouldn't have pulled out a container of already crushed up oreos. The other places I've been to places 2 whole oreos on the frozen plate and then pours chocolate or vanilla milk.  Not chocolate syrup!

resp.text: Hello, we are sorry you had a negative experience! Thank you for your feedback! We have corrected the issues highlighted. The fatty residue is because we use fresh cream, milk and Sugar in our icecream base so it gives that rich homemade flavor, please come back and give us a try and we can make it right for you!

name: Stephani Alsop
text: Extremely delicious ice cream 😍 SUPER friendly staff! Love this place

resp.text: Thank You Stephani! We are so glad you enjoyed your first time! We can’t wait to see you again and share our love for good food and icecream with you!

name: Hunter Mitchell
text: Ice cream was good. They should livin the place up a bit though

resp.text: Thank You for your kind review Hunter! Yes we are in the process of renovating the space! We just had a couple of setbacks due to Covid.

name: Jennifer Riedel
text: My first visit under the new ownership and the associate was very sweet and professional. There was an issue with my 15% off coupon and she still honored it! I purchased the s'mores ice cream and my father purchased the mango green tea. She was very quick and courteous. The establishment was clean, very nice music playing, and the vibe was chill.

name: cupcake toturial
text: I did not like my drink, and it expensive !

resp.text: We are sorry for your experience Cupcake! Come back and see us to give us a chance to make it right! Please ask for the manager when you come in!

name: James Galbraith
text: Good product, but extremely long wait time after placing order

resp.text: Hello James, we are extremely sorry that you had to wait a long time after placing your order, we always prioritize our service speed and are extremely sorry that we weren’t able to deliver on it, after speaking with the team it was brought to our attention that we were short staffed due to two employees calling out and that contributed to a long wait time when you visited, the staff shortage was resolved soon thereafter when other employees were called in. Please do come back and give us a try again and please accept this coupon for a free order of rolled icecream on us. Just show this response and your ID to the manager or shift leader and we will take care of you! See you soon!

name: Carliese Inman
text: Very good ice cream and friendly staff. Will be returning.

name: Emily B
text: The ice cream is so fun to watch being made. It looks pretty and tastes pretty good too. The kids loooooove going to get ice cream at the Ice Queen. We go often.

name: Brittany Bailey
text: I went with my parents last week. They provided awesome service, and were very willing to answer a million questions. The ice cream is made right in front of your eyes from a fresh custard mix! It's a lot like having sushi made in front of you. They add the flavorings and the chopped up candy/fruit/etc right there as they freeze and form the liquid ice cream on a frozen surface. (See my video) They also make a nitrogen frozen ice cream on the spot too. I didn't try that, but there were lots of kids around who really seemed you be enjoying it. Highly recommended. Great for sharing, since you get several rolls. Toppings are included with no extra charge.

name: SIMPLYBABY G
text: It was delicious made my own strawberry ice cream, toppings: strawberries, pecans, and cupcake bites (balls) and a strawberry sauce 😍💖

name: Fredek Leiningen
text: Great food. Great prices. My buddy got this fajita dish that was ridiculous. Full of shrimp and steak that came out sizzling. Atmosphere was ok. Not much ambiance. That said the food... Wow. Close to Elgin CC too!

name: Chloe Nam
text: This was first time been there and it was so different...and taste was good...♥

name: Breanna Garza
text: I don’t know why Royal Cafe closed down, but I sure wish it hadn’t. It was my favorite place in Columbus to go for ice cream! Went into Ice Queen shortly after they opened....I didn’t even get anything because they changed the menu up SO much!! Now everything that was good is gone. R.I.P. Royal Cafe

name: Johnny Adams
text:
Took my daughter to go try this place and wow were we surprised.
Amazing ice cream. I will definitely be back.

I love taro because its not so sweet but that one tasted like a sugar shack! Lol but I tell you it's the absolute creamiest ice cream I've ever had! Great place

text: This place is really great. Simple formula, but they make the ice creams so well. Staff was very nice as well. We are def coming again.

text: This was my first visit, went with the family.  We had the rolled ice cream.  It was very good! Lots of flavor combinations to choose from. It's prepared right in front of you, fun to watch.  Definitely will be returning in the near future.

text: Her food is really good the ice cream is good. I've had alot of my order wrong due to language barrier. I honestly think the shop would have more business if she worked on that too. The chicken teriyaki with fried rice and vegetables is a hit...her chicken philly's are great too..

resp.text: Hello Mercedes, we believe this review was meant for the previous owner, we do not serve the dishes you mention in your review, we have completely overhauled our menu after taking over in March 2020, we welcome you to give us a try and check out our new menu! We sure hope we can earn a five star rating from you! See you soon!

I had all this after their Italian Philly for lunch .

text: Best experience I have ever had with ice cream. Wish there was a place like this in Indiana!

text: Great taste good quick service also you can watch them make your 🍦 icecream its cool

text: I always saw places like this on YouTube and always wanted to go and now there's this place in Columbus that does the rolled ice cream is amazing. I'm going to have a task where I try every single kind and combination that they serve. Everything from green tea,mango and coffee.

name: Lacy Harden
text: This place has an identity crisis . It's called a cafe and deli but it's actually an ice cream shop . We had no idea until we arrived. The other customers seemed to be enjoying the ice cream but can you really screw up ice cream? The deli part is about 10 items mostly variations of a cheese steak. I asked about the ingredients and the guy obviously didn't know and as another employee walked up, he simply walked off without answering. I asked her the same question and she didn't know either. I mean seriously?!? Overall the service was completely lacking! Obviously no training had been performed. With all that said, the food was actually great once it arrived. I had to go back to ask for ketchup and they had forgotten the coffee purchased. The place also lacked any cleanliness standards for an eatery and there was no place to store the tray from the food.

text: Overall great customer service; it only takes a few minutes to be served after completion of ordering from the menu. The staff is very polite and knowledgeable with any questions you may have on their menu.

text: First time trying rolled ice cream and I loved it. I mean it’s hard to get ice cream wrong. Takes a while especially if there’s already a line but worth the wait.

name: Ashley Dailey
text: The first time I tried Ice Queen was in Lagrange,GA and let me say it was amazing. Being a lover of bubble tea and working for a bubble tea store at one point I was so excited to learn that there was an Ice Queen in Columbus,GA as well! I’ve been there multiple times and while the tea/tapioca pearls are a hit or miss I still go because I like that they don’t use powdered Thai tea, to my knowledge anyways. I also enjoy one girl who seems to always work there and is very friendly and nice( I don’t know her name but she is short and always has hoop earings). I recently went there with my friend (a HOUR and about ten minutes before they closed) and ordered our typical drinks with the tapioca pearls and was told that they didn’t have any. Disappointed because that is one of the biggest reasons for a BUBBLE tea, they did offer strawberry and mango popping boba (which aren’t our favorites due to it being a Thai tea and my friend doesn’t enjoy them at all) and I nicely told them never mind. The girl that was working gave me a really rude/nasty look that almost makes me not want to come back because of it.( this same girl has helped me my first time coming to this location and her friend was behind me and she was very, VERY distracted by that). Besides those things most of my visits here have been pleasant.

text: We Arrived at 11:30 and placed our order. The last two people were served at 1:00 there were 16 of us.  They gave out of French fries after about 6 of of our orders and we were served chips.  There was no ice for the drinks,  we saw several to go orders leave before we were served. The buns were cold.  The servers were nice but not efficient.

text: Delicious ice cream roll ups!  The only thing I would change would be for them to advertise outside and inside on the walls that roll up ice cream is what they do/serve!  We had no idea that’s what it was bc there aren’t any pictures of it anywhere to see and the dominant menu on the wall is for slushes and milk slushes - it doesn’t say “create your own ice cream ROLL UPS” which would make a huge difference bc it’s super fun to watch and delicious to eat. Can’t wait to come back.

text: Placed first order through waitr..OMG..new york hotdog?..How dare you even use the name. And it was suppose to come with fries..didnt happen. The spicy subs were so so..i guess its the ice cream..not the food.

text: Really enjoyable experience. The ice cream was really good. I also really enjoyed watching them create the rolled icecream

Keep it up guys , you are getting famous !
😊🤘👍

text: Unbelievable food . This is a place which caters to everyone . Recommend  the Philly meat on a platter you have to ask for it they will give it on bed of seasoned fries .  Ice cream is out of this world .They roll it and my cousons enjoyed it . Excellent customer service .

name: Gua Pa
text: Customer service here is A+. We've found a new place for great ice cream 🙂🍦🍧🍨.

name: Victoria Rosado-Cohen
text: The ice cream was decent but I expected more for what it was worth. It kinda had a frost bite taste which makes sense considering they rapidly freeze it. Glad I tried it though!

name: Carla Alvarez
text:
It's the little things...
I just left this place with my ice cream, wich I was really looking forward to since everyone has had nothing but good things to say about. The service was nice and quick and the ice cream tasted really good, HOWEVER, as I separated the rolls I noticed the one thing that will make me not want to come back (and the reason for the one star, A HAIR.
This is DISGUSTING!!!
The young man that was doing my ice cream was wearing a cap and wearing gloves, and his hair was blonde not black. Clearly it wasn't his hair. It makes me wonder what else you could find.
It sucks, because this really ruined it for me.

name: Chami Storey
text: Great phillys, yummy rolled ice cream, and great bubble tea. Nice staff and always a great atmosphere.

name: Rave HZ
text: My fiance and I ordered through waitr as we had never tried this place before and wanted to see if it was good due to the reviews. Well I ordered an Italian sub sandwich and it was really greasy and it looked smaller than the picture on Waitr. The fries....they were okay but they were soggy and not at all crispy. It tasted like someone cooked them and then figured it wasn't worth the extra 5 minutes and said it was done. The grilled cheese wasn't even brown and the chicken was a little dry but I think that's Waitrs fault since I'm sure it was juicier when made. The only good thing honestly was the ice cream. I'm just really concerned about the quality of the food and dont know if I'll ever order from Waitr again.

I am a regular customer, Icecream here is really good but i have to give a 2 due to service, i always ask for extra tapioca for smoothie and i am ready to pay few extra bucks. I dont understand why they do this all the time they dont put extra tapioca specially few staff people in the evenings. I am really disappointed as today even though the guy keeps on telling the other girl to put extra tapioca she did not. I wish there is other bubble tea place in columbus.

Only defect of visit was drive through intercom to place your order, screens work but communication device wasn't properly working. I could hardly hear the server on the other end an same I guess her end on the machine. Also number on my stall was unavailable so had to tell the server where I was which was a tad bit annoying.

Price: $$ & 1/2

Pro: clean restrooms upon visit, order was correct, parking lot was presentable, server was respectful.

Con: Order mechanism for drive through wasn't function correctly, had to tell server on intercom which stall I was occupying, intercoms also fizzled an have to raise your voice in order to hear you...

name: Spencer Sumner
text:
NERDtorch cafe is the next big thing for Opelika/Auburn and people that love video games, anime, and all things nerd culture. Nigel and Leilani run the store and are two of my favorite people. They get to know their customers very well and it makes the atmosphere feel like you're walking in to a good friends house to play the day away with some Smash Bros or Halo.

Leilani makes the best tacos I have ever had in my life. If you get the chance, go to Taco Tuesday. You won't regret it. In fact all the food is delicious. An order of double fries or nachos goes perfect with a D&D session.

Nigel has the uncanny ability to bring fun wherever he goes. He's set up the cafe to accommodate nearly any genre of nerd from retro gamers to hardcore tournament competitors. He's also constantly working to improve his business and make sure everyone that walks in the door has a great time. He also runs a pretty dope YouTube channel called Nerd Torch TV.

The store is organized and managed extremely well. There are several rooms dedicated to different types of gaming. There is a room for tabletop games, another for rhythm games like Guitar Hero or DDR, and other rooms dedicated to console games. There's even a PC built for gaming. Multiplayer games are very popular and this is a great place to find people that love to play Smash. I don't think I've ever been to the cafe when there wasn't someone playing Smash or Mario Cart. There's a great community built up around the cafe as well. All of the cafe members are invited to a GroupMe chat where you can get updates on events or just chat and hang out. This year, they organized a secret santa for everyone.

If you love games, nerds, and having a good time then you won't be dissapointed if drop by NERDtorch Cafe.

resp.text: Thanks so much for writing such a detailed description of NERDtorch Cafe! It means a lot that you would go to such efforts to show your appreciation like this. I'm glad we have you in our community and I know you'll keep making D&D nights awesome.

name: Becca H
text:
Wow, I just read through some reviews of this place and I'm not sure what is going on or how it could have this high rating. First, we all know that Covid has happened and I've given this place chance after chance this past year in hopes that maybe, this time things would be different. Today, I'm just done. This place has weird hours 7am-8pm. So you can choose, do you want breakfast or do you want to make yourself late. That's why it's always empty in the morning for rush hour. Then, they rarely operate the app. Oh, they will tell you it's "down" but then, you'll have an employee like I got today who quickly replied yes when I asked if that was done purposely. She said they were "short-handed" The only way you could order was to go through the drive thru, all of the drive ups had signs that said "Sorry :-( Drive thru only."
So, I gave it a chance anyway seeing as my order was being taken by someone outside to make me feel like I was at chick-fil-a ...
I waited through the line, which was wrapped all the way around the building, it moved fairly quickly. I thought well nothing else is working for them, so maybe this is a good thing. Got to the window, was given the wrong amount to pay but after fumbling the young lady got my order correct and took my card. Then, while waiting for receipt, I was again offered the wrong food this time, but what looked like a perplexed manager of sorts. Almost as if she wanted to argue for a second, how could I be the wrong car, lol... Um, yes, I managed to jump line in my car. Eyes rolling, then I was finally given my order and it was lukewarm, my tea was watered down and my food was not good. Now, I know it sounds like I'm being a total @ss but honestly I'm not, see this happens at this location ... all... the... time! I've waited forever for food at the drive up and then been handed food that a 10 year old could better prepare. I'm not sure if it's an employee retention problem, a management issue, or just simply that no one here cares. One would think, after a nice renovation that management would put in a little effort. I can honestly say, I have lived in Pelham for 13 years. My kids grew up coming to this spot after ballgames, late night snacks, etc and the food was always good. Not sure why they even redone this restaurant because it has been horrible since day one of their new re-opening. Anyone who eats at Sonic normally goes for the drive up. I could care less about the drive thru or the inside. Also, was great because you could go at 10pm at night for a treat. Whoever is running this location needs to do better but I for one, have given it my last go. Do yourself a favor and if you are craving sonic, go to another location.

resp.text: We're sorry to hear you had a negative experience with one of our locations. If you would like to escalate your feedback to the franchise owner, our team is happy to file a report. We encourage you to give us a call at 1-888-257-8100 or visit http://bit.ly/1EOeLMc whenever you have time.

name: Subie Chik
text: The new renovations are nice, but they did not add enough parking for the dine-in customers, so people have to park at the drive in ordering boxes to go inside & order. The staff was very uninformed on the menu & what options they no longer carried. We went in & I ordered a family size tot for my family & it showed on the ordering screen "family tot" with the appropriate price. I paid at the order box & our food came out quickly, but in a smaller bag than we were expecting. I asked the waitress about the family order of tots & she said it wasn't an option & so she gave me a large size order. Instead of asking if I would like a refund or a different size tot, she said she would ask her manager about it. She came back about 30 seconds later & said the manager refunded the difference & she walked off before I could say another word. I feel the waitress & manager were extremely rude for not properly informing us & giving us an option for something different. I never even saw the manager since the interior "eat in" area is just like ordering outside in your car. The staff needs better training & the store needs a better manager instead of the one they have! They need a manager who acts like a manager instead of hiding behind wall & making the food runners do his work for him. The manager should have personally come out to explain the situation to us & try to remedy the problem! We will not be back!
