Then they said we could have one order.. then after we explained the situation the lady said, "we can do it only this time". We said okay and we're fine with that. They then only rung up 2 orders and said they could only do two for now that we could get the others "another time". But then they wouldn't give vouchers for the other two. They said their manager is on vacation and they would have to ask him when he got back. The cashier denied ever saying that they could do it this time. After about 15 minutes they finally agreed to honor their voucher. Also ordered a chicken sandwich with no mayo and no tomato.. this was discussed three times and my sandwich still had tomato. According to the receipt the cashier's name was Samantha. I will not be back to this location. Very dissatisfied.

text: The COOKIES are awesome!!!!! The staff is HORRIBLE!!!! I drive from Elmore County on a regular basis for these cookies seeing how this is the closest location to me. I’ve been to this location several times.... Each time, there has been different employees however, they ALL have had the same attitude which is extremely RUDE & UNPROFESSIONAL!

resp.text: Hi Veronica!  I am so sorry that these experiences have not been as expected.  We will escalate this feedback to our leadership and ensure the team is trained appropriately.  Thank you so much for taking the time to leave this feedback!

name: Phillip C.
text:
I understand limiting store capacity because of the virus, but the amount of time we had to wait outside in roughly 30 degree weather almost caused us to go elsewhere... and I really wish we had. I've bought better chocolate chip cookies from Kroger in a pack of 25 for $2.50. Also I would have expected Praline Pecan ice cream to have more pecans and not be half melted before I even began to eat it. Only reason this isn't a 1 star rating is the cookies weren't terrible. If you want better cookies go to Kroger, and for a cookie ice cream sandwich go to Brusters... and for the icing filled one, just get a double doozie from the cookie place in the mall. You could probably buy all three of those and still save money too.

Oh, and they deliver but can't do to go orders? How does that even make sense?

name: Bailey Ray
text: Worst place to order from, hands down. Staff is rude and will hang up on you for calling to check in on your order. If I could give them negative stars, I would.

name: Wes Harris
text: Did an online order and 3 weeks later,  the order still had not shipped. I had to really search to find a number to call and see what happened to the order. We never got an explanation or apology. We were told the credit card we be refunded in 3 to 5 days. Good cookies but terrible company to deal with. Very disapointed.

name: Lexie Schoenrock
text: Horrible delivery service. Got the wrong cookies once. Second time, the cookies never came. Called the next day and they said they would deliver them at 2 pm. Those never came either. Called and they said they didn’t have a driver that day. Absolutely ridiculous. Just make your own cookies.

name: Joyce Curry
text: How can you go wrong with cookies... especially when they are served warm! They have plenty of varieties too.

name: Albert Wang
text: Overpriced cookies. People hyped it up. I tried a bunch of flavors, including the mint, macadamia, and the cookies and creme. I have to say it taste like a cookie. It is definitely soft and warm but that's because it's served out of the oven. I would visit more often if the prices at least reflect the quality I'm looking for. Like don't get me wrong, their cookies are fine. But like I'd rather buy Pepperidge farm and reheat it in a small cookie oven. Where it's 8 for 2.99 than 1 for 1.50

name: Andrew Painton
text: The gentleman tonight made me a loyal customer and deserves a raise! I ordered a specialty cookie and two others very close to closing time which needed to be made fresh so I waited out in my car. Upon my surprise I looked up shortly after and there he was walking down the sidewalk in the pouring rain to bring me my cookies. Great job!

name: Myandi Flowers-Brasher
text:
It took about 30 minutes to get my cookies (though i do live on the edge of their delivery area). The cookies were still soft and were a little warmer than room temperature. Super yummy though. I'll definitely order from them again, especially if I'm on campus.

01/18/2020 Edit: Cookies are great, the wait is not. Make sure your order AT LEAST an hour before you need the cookies. This is especially important if you live in a residential area and not downtown/on campus. Good cookies, bad wait. Delivery time 30 minutes, have been waiting an hour and still no cookies. Their storefront is less than fifteen minutes from my house. Just called, my deliver driver is biking to my apartment. The store needs to updates their delivery times to reflect their driver's speed. It's good that they're employing bikers though.

name: Victoria Shinnick
text: Told my cookies would take 35-45 minutes, but were still “baking” two hours later and had no update on my tracking.The location is 5 minutes down the road. I ended up cancelling my order and getting a refund. I understand being short staffed, but two hours is a bit ridiculous, and I wish that the time would’ve been better communicated.

name: Will Burns
text: Absolutely horrible. my roommate and i just ordered cookies and it took almost two hours to arrive. 6 cookies. but whatever we got them. THEN we go up to our DORM ROOM and IMAGINE OUR SURPRISE when they don’t even GIVE US 2 OF OUR COOKIES. i DO NOT RECOMMEND it’d be faster to BUY COOKIE MIX and BAKE YOUR OWN COOKIES. id give 0 stars if possible.

name: Austin Folsom (thejaustin)
text: Highly appreciate the service and staff of this location. The staff was friendly and I respect the decision to turn away those without a mask, as this is the first time I've actually seen it enforced at any form of store I've been to. As someone whose experienced family loss due to covid-induced symptoms, I love to see the policy upheld.

name: Janae Lacy
text: Loved it and the cookies are freaking awesome nice and warm when you get them a must stop by😍😍😘😘🥰🥰

name: Madeleine Williams
text: DO NOT ORDER from here! I ordered 6 cookies, and after two hours of them not arriving (on a Tuesday night- not even a weekend), I tried to call over and over again. By midnight, I finally had to go to bed and the next morning, I come to find my order was never even delivered, no phone call, no email, NOTHING. When I spend that much on cookies, I expect to actually receive them OR be refunded.. Still am not able to get in contact with anyone about my issue because they won't answer the phone.

name: Jeremy Yount
text: My address is exactly 5ft outside their delivery zone... if they are going to advertise delivery, maybe they should have a delivery range that goes just a little bit further than the dorm halls. Will be buying cookies from Walmart from now on.

name: Matthew Stewart
text: Favorite cookie franchise. They're always so busy cause it's literally so good. Worth the wait every time . You've been warned

name: Madison Gaston
text: Worst delivery/customer service I have ever experienced. Won’t be surprised if this business goes under in the near future. I guess they will give anybody a GM job these days.

name: Tiffany Miller
text: My experience was absolutely horrible. We ordered cookies last night for delivery, and they never showed up!! We called and called...no answer every time. After waiting 4 hours for them (the tracker still said they were on "bake" by the way), we gave up. Customer service finally emailed us back and is giving us a refund and a cookie coupon. This was the worst customer service I have ever experienced. This was my first time ordering from this place, but never again.

name: sanower warsi
text: Worse service, I can buy better ice-cream from DQ. Waited 2 hr but still didn't get my order.

name: Zach Lodigensky
text: Worst service ever. After 30 minutes of waiting I get an email saying I have to call because there was a problem. After waiting on hold for 10 minutes I’m told they have no delivery people and the store tells me they called me which they never did. Not sure why it took 30 minutes for them to realize they had not delivery people and why they couldn’t just call me and tell me when they had my contact information.

name: David Williams
text: Don’t waste your time here. Sat in line for over 20 mins to have them tell me they only take cash... won’t be going back!

name: Autumn Reynolds
text: Pretty good cookies. About $2 each. Always served warm. Usually out of top flavors when I visit. Doing way better than I thought it would as a business.

name: Nathan Pipkin
text: If there is going to be a multiple hour delay on a small order of cookies going 5 minutes down the road, maybe clarify that before someone puts in an order. Poor customer service, sub par cookies and a waste of time.

name: Emisha RodriguezDickey
text: If I could give this zero stars I would .. I’m visiting the area placed a deliver order at 5:45 pm it’s 8:30 pm and it’s still not delivered .. I ordered one ☝🏽 cookie and 2 small ice creams. This is the worse service I have ever received called customer service and they gave me a coupon to get 3 free cookies If I BUY 3 that is the sorriest compensation for not receiving quality customer service..

name: Shenita Hunter
text: Really love love love these cookies!!! The Snickerdoodle cookies are heavenly!!! The service was mediocre. The 4 stars are for the cookies alone!!

name: Steven Penny
text:
I had an order for pickup, I sat in my car and waited for the pickup time. I was using the order tracking function and after 25 minutes past the pickup time, it still said “baking” so I went into the store. I waited in line and was told they were out of the cookies I wanted, they just sold out of them. I asked why they didn’t make my order before and was told they put orders together when someone arrives, what is the purpose then of pickup and tracking? They were even out of regular chocolate....how simple of a business model is it to bake cookies? They’re expensive cookies...you’d figure they’d have incentive to keep them available.

Also, your delivery drivers have no right to park in the handicapped spots.

name: lucas frAley
text: We ordered cookies first thing in the morning from here for a 1p.m. arrival time,  and they never arrived. We called and were put on a corporate hold for 20 min. Then they said the cookies were on their way (1:30p.m.). We waited 30 more minutes and the location is only 4 minutes from our house. They still never arrived. We called and canceled and that took us and additional 20 mins to do that.

name: Julie B
text: I placed an order for cookies at 10:04pm. At 11:46pm I was told the delivery guy had just left with my order and it was out for delivery. Waited...... so now it’s 12:24am and still have no cookies. I canceled my order. This is very horrible service!!!

name: Harrison B.
text:
I see a lot of bad reviews on service and time for delivery...I cant say much since both times I ordered I did it hours earlier at work to have them delivered shortly after I get home. Which, honestly, I love being able to do ahead of time easy unlike most delivery services.

Prices are a bit high, but I always look for and use deals. And when they arrived....oh man, were they delicious. I've actually seem people complain they were still soft and warm. How? They literally melt in your mouth. I'd say worth $2 at normal price even though they arent huge. Go buy those cheap Grandma cookies or a pack of oreos if you just wanna eat a cookie for the sake of it

name: Jeremy Edwards
text: I came just to look at the place and they wouldn’t serve me because I didn’t have a mask on.  There was no food out or anything.   I could have had corona all over my hands but since I didn’t have a mask on I couldn’t  get anything.    I have never eaten here and by the looks at it I never will.    We are headed for full blown facism.   THIS place will never get my money!!!!!!

name: Jermarion Walker
text: Good 🍪

name: Sydney Stewart
text: Best cookies I’ve had in my life. Melt in your mouth delicious. Always warm.

name: Mandy Byrd
text: A pregnant woman’s dream come true. The cookies were perfect!

name: Auburn S
text: These cookies are pricey but they are so good. My favorite is the smores cookie.

name: Michele Thomas
text: I ordered a cookie delivery at 930 pm. It said 30-40 delivery. 2 hours later, 2 calls trying to reach the store and being on hold for over an hour between the calls, they couldn't tell me when the order would be delivered. They kept telling me they were going to be going out for delivery. The delivery person was even at the apartment complex and left without delivery of the cookies!!

name: Jonas Bowersock
text: Perfectly delicious cookies

name: Jared Hinkle
text: Absolutely love the cookies!!

name: Joshua Berry
text: The bomb...period

name: Jennifer “jenexecsec421” Collins
text: This was my second time ordering delivery. We live not even 5mins from the place and it took well over an hour both times. Fine, I can be patient, I'm never in a hurry, otherwise I would just go in. Well tonight I ordered, took over an hour and the person rang the doorbell and ran. Have it on video bc well its 2020. I literally got right up. Person left the cookies sitting on the ground. What if I hadn't heard the bell on the first ring? My cookies would just be sitting there. I'm going to stop tipping during online checkout, thats ridiculous.

name: Danielle Hayes
text:
It was 8:30 on a Friday night and my little girl’s icecream from dinner got eaten by a family member while she was getting ready for bed. She was so upset. I wanted to end our night on a good note. I remembered seeing this cookie store downtown that night and was excited to discover they deliver.
I ordered six cookies for our family and an icecream for her. While waiting I read reviews and was waiting to have to wait a long time. Ten minutes after ordering I get a call from the store telling me my order was ready with the exception of one cookie flavor. They offered to bake me one if I wanted to wait or substitute another one and be on their way. I chose to substitute, and ten minutes later they were at my door with warm cookies and cold Icecream. My daughter loved her cookie dough icecream and my husband and I enjoyed breaking off a few pieces of cookie to try (so warm and good. Crunchy on the edges, but nice and soft/gooey in the middle) before making ourselves save them for the kids to enjoy tomorrow. FAST delivery, and a really good bad decision to make late at night.

name: Jenni McDonough
text: Place was packed at 10:30 pm on a Thursday.  Out of choc chip, white chocolate and sugar cookies.😭. $20 for 6 cookies and milk

name: Miles Copeland
text: Takes a really long time to get delivered but is really good and cookies were still warm.

name: Destiny Headley
text: Be aware that even if you are not medically able to wear a mask and even if you are the only person inside they will not serve you because you aren’t wearing a mask

name: Patrick Davidson
text: Been waiting two hours for my cookies and they don’t answer the phone

name: Brady Nell Johnson
text: I love insomnia cookies and they are very good!! I also understand that this new location is very busy, especially in this college town! But I ordered some cookies at 10:30 pm and for them to be delivered at 12:30 am (so I ordered 2 hours ahead). I also respected their possible up to 55 minute delivery time, but when it was around 1:45 am I called to see if I would be getting my cookies and they said i’d be next out whenever a driver is available. It is now 2:15 am and they close at 3, and my cookies haven’t even been picked up by a driver (I tracked them). I don’t ever leave reviews but this was kind of annoying. I suppose I won’t be getting my cookies tonight so they will just deliver tomorrow or I won’t get them at all? idk. All I can say is the cookies are great but go inside to pick them up or make sure you order at-least 4 hours ahead bc tonight I wasted my money, waited a long time, and didn’t even get them.

name: Allen Adams
text: Expensive for cookies but dang if they aren't good.  Will go back again for their "served still warm" melty chocolate goodness....

name: Bridgette Walker
text: No good 😕

name: Caroline Conn
text: Takes several hours even if doing curbside delivery.

text: terrible service but good-ish cookies. GO TO MYLKS ON WEST MAGNOLIA.

text: 11pm cookies after studying and doing homework hit the best.

text: Ordered 2 hours ago and still haven’t gotten them yet:( Website says they are “baking”🤔

text: The lady working was completely rude. Only 5 people are allowed in at a time and she made us wait outside for 10 minutes while her roommate socialized with friends inside.

name: PEYTON HOWE
text: My family does their best to give everyone the best ice cream in the WORLD!  If your wondering i'm the dishwasher at Freezes Creamery! xD. Thanks everyone for coming out to Freezes Creamery and having ice cream.

text: Awesome food, very nice staff members, consistently great ambience. They charge convenient pricing and the food quality is awesome. Kudos.

name: Alex Sizemore
text: Holy !@#$ that's good 🍦

name: Hayden Gray
text: This is an amazing little place! I’ve had some of the best I’ve cream of my life from here. To top it off, the staff are so friendly and welcoming. Keep up the great work!

name: Dan Porter

name: Glenda M. Ross
text: The restuarant I yesterday was not Brain Freeze Ice Cream. Instead it was Refinded To Go. The food was ABSOLUTELY DELICIOUS!

name: Christian Nahrgang

name: Megan Johnson
text: The most delicious ice cream sundaes and shakes, delicious combinations, awesome small town customer service, family owned. Love this place!

name: BLAKE HOWE
text: Love it!!!

name: Bert Davis
text: One of the best, if not the best creamery, i have ever been to. Although you can’t go wrong with anything on their menu, I highly recommend their boozy ice creams!!
